<title>JAPAN: IGS files for bankruptcy.</title>
<headline>IGS files for bankruptcy.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>IGS Corp, a mid-sized software developer, said on Friday that it had filed for bankruptcy at the Tokyo District Court.</p>
<p>It said in a statement that it had total debts of about 5.6 billion yen.</p>
<p>In February, IGS applied for court mediation with its creditors, seeking to rebuild its business under court protection.</p>
<p>&quot;We applied for court mediation and we were trying to restructure our business. But severe financial difficulties forced us to give up hopes of remaining in business and we filed for bankruptcy at the court today,&quot; IGS said on Friday.</p>
<p>Most IGS employees will be transferred to another software developer, Fuji Soft ABC Inc, IGS said.</p>
<p>The Japan Securities Dealers' Association (JSDA) said earlier on Friday that trade in IGS shares had been suspended on the over-the-counter market for the whole day.</p>
<p>The JSDA took the action after rumours emerged that IGS had filed for bankruptcy.</p>
